    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1963-09-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1963-09-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="90"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d90">
                <head>90. Paper Prepared by the Assistant Secretary of State for Far Eastern Affairs
                        (<persName corresp="#p_HRJ1">Hilsman</persName>)<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d90fn1">Source: Kennedy Library, <persName corresp="#p_HRJ1"
                            >Hilsman</persName> Papers, Countries, Vietnam, Undated. Secret. There
                        is no drafting information on the source text, but this is apparently the
                        second paper <persName>Bundy</persName> asked <persName corresp="#p_HRJ1"
                            >Hilsman</persName> to prepare; <ref target="#d85">see Document
                        85</ref>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1963-09-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 11, 1963</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">POSSIBLE POLITICAL PRESSURE WEAPONS FOR USE AGAINST <persName
                        corresp="#p_DIEM1">DIEM</persName> AND <persName corresp="#p_NHU1"
                        >NHU</persName>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Decision of Afro-Asian group to raise <gloss target="#t_GVN1">GVN</gloss>
                        repressive measures at regular session of UNGA.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Statement by the U.S. to <persName corresp="#p_DIEM1">Diem</persName>
                        and/or publicly to the effect that U.S. demands that the <gloss
                            target="#t_GVN1">GVN</gloss> cease the use of all U.S.-supplied
                        equipment for the repression of non-Communists. Institution of end-use
                        checks to determine whether our demand is being complied with.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Appropriately timed leaks on <persName corresp="#p_NHU1">Nhu</persName>’s
                        contacts with the <gloss target="#t_DRV1">DRV</gloss> to effect that
                            <persName corresp="#p_NHU1">Nhu</persName> is selling out to the
                        Communists.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>Suspension of <gloss target="#t_CAS1">CAS</gloss> programs in support of
                        the <gloss target="#t_GVN1">GVN</gloss>.</item>
                    <label>5.</label>
                    <item>Evacuation of American dependents from Viet-Nam.</item>
                    <label>6.</label>
                    <item>As a follow-up to Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HRJ1">Hilsman</persName>’s
                        cable re Senate sentiment on Viet-Nam,<note n="2" xml:id="d90fn2">
                            <ref target="#d63">Document 63</ref>.</note> a cable on Senator
                            <persName corresp="#p_CF1">Church</persName>’s statement that he will
                        introduce resolution to stop aid to Viet-Nam unless <gloss target="#t_GVN1"
                            >GVN</gloss> changes its repressive nature.</item>
                    <label>7.</label>
                    <item>Removal of wraps on <persName corresp="#p_TQ1">Tri Quang</persName> so
                        that press can interview him. Purpose: to get across to the public that
                            <gloss target="#t_GVN1">GVN</gloss> gestures toward the Buddhists are
                        meaningless and to demonstrate to <persName corresp="#p_DIEM1"
                            >Diem</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_NHU1">Nhu</persName> that
                        U.S. may consider <persName corresp="#p_TQ1">Tri Quang</persName> a
                        political alternative.</item>
                    <pb facs="0207" n="181" xml:id="pg_181"/>
                    <label>8.</label>
                    <item>Informing the press that U.S. visa being issued to Foreign Minister
                            <persName corresp="#p_VVM1">Vu Van Mau</persName>.</item>
                </list>
            </div>
